=Description=

"Community Indicators Victoria aims to support equitable, healthy, engaged and well planned communities. Community Indicators Victoria provides a comprehensive framework of community wellbeing measured by local level data. Our wellbeing indicator data can be accessed by our Wellbeing Reports, Live Reports or Data Maps.

Community indicators are a democratic resource for engaging citizens and communities in informed discussions about shared goals and priorities, a policy resource guiding evidence-based planning and action to address the issues identified as important by communities, and a reporting resource tracking and communicating progress towards agreed goals and outcomes.

CIV is a collaborative project within the Place, Health and Liveability Research Program at the McCaughey VicHealth Centre, within the School of Population & Global Health, at the University of Melbourne."

